# Design Tokens

This project uses a design token system defined in `.specs/design-system/tokens.md`.

## Token Reference

When implementing UI, use these token names rather than hardcoded values:

### Colors
- `color-background` - Near-black app background
- `color-surface` - Card/panel backgrounds
- `color-surface-elevated` - Elevated surfaces, modals
- `color-work` - Active/work state (coral-orange)
- `color-rest` - Rest state (mint-teal)
- `color-paused` - Paused state (warm yellow)
- `color-text` - Primary text (white)
- `color-text-secondary` - Muted text
- `color-error` - Error states
- `color-success` - Success states
- `color-warning` - Warning states

### Typography
- `font-display` - Timer numbers (JetBrains Mono)
- `font-body` - Body text (Outfit)
- `text-timer-giant` - Main countdown (8rem)
- `text-timer-large` - Secondary timer (4rem)
- `text-xs` through `text-5xl` - Font size scale

### Spacing
- `spacing-1` through `spacing-24` - Spacing scale

### Border Radius
- `radius-sm`, `radius-md`, `radius-lg`, `radius-xl`, `radius-2xl`, `radius-full`

### Shadows
- `shadow-sm`, `shadow-md`, `shadow-lg`
- `shadow-glow-work`, `shadow-glow-rest` - State glow effects

### Transitions
- `transition-fast` - 150ms for micro-interactions
- `transition-normal` - 250ms standard
- `transition-slow` - 400ms for state changes
- `transition-state` - 800ms for work/rest transitions

## Implementation Guidelines

### Tailwind CSS (with custom config)
```jsx
<button className="bg-work text-white rounded-md px-4 py-2 shadow-glow-work">
  Start Work
</button>
```

### CSS Variables
```css
.timer {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: var(--text-timer-giant);
  color: var(--color-work);
  text-shadow: var(--shadow-glow-work);
}
```

## When Building UI

1. Reference tokens from `.specs/design-system/tokens.md`
2. Use token names in ASCII mockups
3. Implement using actual token values
4. Ensure high contrast for tablet viewing from across room
